HEADWORD: Plasmin
<hw>Plas"min</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>A proteid body, separated by some physiologists from
blood plasma. It is probably identical with fibrinogen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

